    "### Path\n",
    "\n",
    "1) dummies and/or encoding for categorical variables \n",
    "- categorical_ordinal_var :\n",
    "columns CAEC, CALC: no, Sometimes, Frequently, Always\n",
    "columns family_history_with_overwieght, SMOKE, SCC, FAVC : no, yes\n",
    "column MTRANS: Walking, Bike, Public_Transportation, Motobike, Automobile\n",
    "column NOBeyesdad (it is also the target): Insufficient_Weight, Normal_Weight, Overweight_Level_I, Overweight_Level_II, Obesity_Type_I, Obesity_Type_II, Obesity_Type_III\n",
    "\n",
    "- categorical_nominal_var :\n",
    "column Gender: Female, Male\n",
    "\n",
    "2) features will need to be those dummies columns + numrical columns all together, target will be NOBeyesdad\n",
    "3) at some point I need to know which variables are the most correlated to each other and with the target column - find a way \n",
    "4) Then we scale the data using StandardScaler()\n",
    "5) Then we can do a KNNClassifier with k=5\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 32,
   "id": "080aff99-e578-4614-8c4e-7a1b412106ce",
   "metadata": {},
